<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="60" pageId="2" pageNumber="59" type="description">
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Description.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Female.</emphasis>
Total length 1.85-2 mm. (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
). Head and mesosoma black, metasoma completely dark reddish brown. Antennae brown, mandibles, wings venation and legs yellowish brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Head</emphasis>
(Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1-3</figureCitation>
) in anterior view as high as wide. Malar sulci simple. Antenna (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
) with 13 segments, pilose, subcylindrical, flagellomeres 1 and 2 subequal in length, F6 to F11 moniliform, club consisting of six flagellomeres, with rhinaria. Posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">2</figureCitation>
, see arrow). 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Pronotum</emphasis>
. Pronotal plate (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">2</figureCitation>
) wide, striate in anterior half as well as bridge that connect this half with posterior half. Posterior half with row of setae, lateral foveae open. Dorsal margin emarginate. Pronotal ridge absent. Sides of pronotum convex, with a pubescent area on upper half of ventral margin (beneath pronotal plate).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Mesoscutum.</emphasis>
Strongly convex in profile (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
). Parapsidal ridges represented by hair lines (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">3</figureCitation>
). Parascutal impressions incomplete. Notauli absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Mesopectus</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
). Upper part and lower part of mesopleuron smooth, glabrous. Mesopleural carina simple. Precoxal carina present. Subalar pit narrow and shallow. Mesopleural triangle undefined. Surcoxal depression absent.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Mesoscutellum</emphasis>
. Scutellar foveae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">3</figureCitation>
) deep, large, wider than long. Lateral bars of scutellum striate. Dorsal surface of scutellum (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">3</figureCitation>
) areolate-punctate, posterior margin bluntly rounded. Scutellar plate (Figs 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">2</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">3</figureCitation>
) suboval, posterior margin rounded, dorsal surface with midpit placed close to posterior margin of plate, with punctures on each side, with single setae in each one.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Metapectal-propodeal complex</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
). Posteroventral corner of metapleuron flat, rounded and pubescent, anteroventral cavity subcircular, setose. Propodeum covered with long, apressed setae. Lateral propodeal carinae semiparalell.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="2" pageNumber="59">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">Wings</emphasis>
. Forewings hyaline (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="2" pageNumber="59">1</figureCitation>
), apical margin with hair fringe, basal margin lacking hair fringe, with membrane pubescence mostly reduced hair bases, marginal cell closed, longer than wide.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<pageBreakToken pageId="3" pageNumber="60" start="start">Legs</pageBreakToken>
</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">1</figureCitation>
). Fore and mid coxa subequal in size, variously setose, hind coxa about twice the size of either fore or mid coxae, with a patch of woolly setae on posterior margin. Femora and tibiae sparsely setose, tibiae with more apprised setae; tarsomeres covered with dense appressed setae.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Metasoma</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">1</figureCitation>
). Base of syntergum with hairy ring completed, remainder of metasoma glabrous.
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="3" pageNumber="60">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">Male.</emphasis>
Similar to female. Male antennae (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 1–4" captionStartId="F1" captionText="Figures 1 - 4. Holotype of Euxestophaga argentinensis Gallardo sp. n. Female. 1 Habitus (lateral view) 2 Head and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates posterior margin of gena distinct, but not carinata 3 Head (posterior view) and mesosoma (dorsal view), arrow indicates basal margin of forewing lacking hair fringe. Male 4 Antenna, arrow indicates posterior margin of scutellum bluntly rounded." figureDoi="10.3897/jhr.54.10096.figures1-4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/124108" pageId="3" pageNumber="60">4</figureCitation>
) filiform, 15 segments, F1 curved, longer than following flagellomeres, F2 shorter than other flagellomeres. Metasoma nearly squared posteriorly in lateral view. Metasoma completely dark reddish brown or ventrally yellowish brown. Base of syntergum with hairy ring interrupted apically.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
